#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.32:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:0.2"
msgid "3. Sabbavagga"
msgstr "3. All"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 32. Dutiyasamugghātasappāyasutta → dutiyasappāyapaṭipadāsuttaṃ (bj) | sappāya 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Dutiyasamugghātasappāyasutta"
msgstr "32. The Practice Conducive to Uprooting (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:1.1"
msgid "“Sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all "
"identifying."

msgctxt "sn35.32:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn35.32:1.3"
msgid "Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:2.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.32:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn35.32:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā … pe …"
msgstr "“Are sights …"

msgctxt "sn35.32:8.2"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr "eye consciousness …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:9.1"
msgid "cakkhusamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?"
msgstr "eye contact …"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:9.2"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante” … pe …."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.32:10.1"
msgid ""
"“Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye "
"contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
